You can get the `brandId` of a brand in Shopify by following these steps:

1. Log in to your Shopify store as an admin.
2. Go to Products > Brands (or whatever you named your brand taxonomy).
3. Click on the brand whose ID you want to get.
4. Look at the URL in your browser's address bar. The brand ID is the number at the end of the URL after /admin/brands/.

For example, if the URL is `https://yourshop.myshopify.com/admin/brands/1234567890`, then the brand ID is `1234567890`.

Alternatively, you can use the Shopify REST Admin API to retrieve a list of brands or a specific brand by name. Here's an example code snippet:

```
const shopUrl = 'yourshop.myshopify.com';
const accessToken = 'your_access_token';
const brandName = 'Your brand name';

fetch(`https://${shopUrl}/admin/api/2022-01/brands.json?name=${encodeURIComponent(brandName)}`, {
  headers: {
    'Content-Type': 'application/json',
    'X-Shopify-Access-Token': accessToken
  }
})
  .then(response => response.json())
  .then(data => {
    const brands = data.brands;
    const brand = brands.find(b => b.name === brandName);
    const brandId = brand ? brand.id : null;
    console.log(`Brand ID: ${brandId}`);
  })
  .catch(error => console.error(error));
```

